parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel level sensor can cause the fuel gauge to malfunction, leading to inaccurate readings, and potentially causing the vehicle to run out of fuel, stall, or be involved in an accident.
symptoms: The fuel gauge reads empty or fluctuates randomly
the fuel gauge does not register the correct fuel level
the vehicle stalls or runs out of fuel
the check engine light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various components to malfunction, including the fuel gauge, speedometer, and headlights, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The headlights or other lights malfunction
the speedometer or odometer does not work
the fuel gauge malfunctions
the vehicle's electrical system fails
causing various components to malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall or run out of fuel, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or runs out of fuel
the fuel pump fails
causing the vehicle to lose power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power lift gate can cause injury or accident due to the gate's sudden and uncontrolled movement.
symptoms: The power lift gate opens and closes suddenly
nearly hitting the user
and cannot be used due to the failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause loss of control, accidents, and injury.
symptoms: The vehicle skips or jerks when the brakes are applied
and the brakes may not function properly
leading to a bumpy ride.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause loss of vital information, leading to accidents or unsafe driving conditions.
symptoms: The speedometer
gas gauge
oil gauge
and other instruments on the dashboard fail to function or display incorrect information.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the spare tire hoist can cause difficulty or inability to change a flat tire, leading to unsafe driving conditions.
symptoms: The spare tire hoist fails to crank or release the spare tire
making it difficult or impossible to change a flat tire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning system can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, leading to unsafe driving conditions.
symptoms: The air conditioning system stops working
and the condenser may leak or fail
causing the system to lose power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause loss of control, accidents, and injury.
symptoms: The transmission fails
leaving the vehicle stuck or unable to move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wipers can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents or unsafe driving conditions.
symptoms: The windshield wipers do not work consistently or at all
making it difficult to see while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the jack can cause difficulty or inability to change a flat tire, leading to unsafe driving conditions.
symptoms: The jack is inadequate for the vehicle and cannot be used on certain surfaces
making it difficult or impossible to change a flat tire.

symptoms: The brakes are soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels a long distance before applying pressure

the vehicle has an extended stopping distance
the ABS light comes on
the brakes lock up intermittently.

the vehicle has an extended stopping distance
